SEYMOUR v. McDANIEL.† (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. December 26, 1911.) No. 2,194. In Error to the Circuit Court of the United States for the Eastern District of Texas. J. Q. Mahaffey, for plaintiff in error. Hiram Glass, W. L. Estes, and John J. King, for defendant in error.

Before PARDEE and SHELBY, Circuit Judges, and GRUBB, District Judge.

Rehearing denied January 30, 1912.

 PER CURIAM.

We are of the opinion that there is no reversible error shown by the record. Affirmed.
